{"title":"Campy Record Expands Italian Wireless 13sp Gruppo Platform at 37% Lower Price than SR!","link":"https://bikerumor.com/campagnolo-record-13-wireless-road-and-gravel-groupset/","date":1777464000000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-18-1536x1024.jpg\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1024\" alt=\"Campagnolo Record 2x crank\" /></p>\n<p>Enter Campagnolo Record 13 wireless. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>After two separate <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/?s=campagnolo+super+record\" target=\"_blank\">Super Record</a> launches last year, Campagnolo is back for 2026 with a whole suite of 1x and 2x 13-speed Record wireless groupsets that are a lot more affordable. With five different road, all-road, and gravel gruppo configurations available, the new wireless Campagnolo Record 13 platform costs 37% less than Super Record, saving buyers 1200-1600€ with just a couple hundred grams of added weight to show for it. You get much of the same classy angular carbon good looks, the super-fast wireless electronic shifting, mix-and-match wireless 13-speed compatibility with or without a clutched rear derailleur, excellent proven braking, and those same made-in-Italy vibes. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Just now, it’ll cost you a lot less.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Campagnolo Record 13 wireless road and gravel groupset</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-17.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2500\" height=\"1667\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-17.jpg\" alt=\"Campagnolo Record 2x crank\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-17.jpg 2500w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-17-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-17-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-17-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-17-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-17-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-17-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-17-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-17-1350x900.jpg 1350w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Everything you loved about Super Record, but now at the Record level for 5/8 of the price. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s still not quite as cheap as <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/sram-force-rival-12-axs-13-axs-xplr-prices-actual-weights/\" target=\"_blank\">Force XPLR</a> or <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/shimano-dura-ace-and-ultegra-deliver-fastest-shifting-ever-with-wireless-12-speed-groups/\" target=\"_blank\">Ultegra</a>. But Record is now a lot more affordable than either <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/sram-red-xplr-13-speed-groupset/\" target=\"_blank\">Red XPLR</a> or <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/shimano-dura-ace-and-ultegra-deliver-fastest-shifting-ever-with-wireless-12-speed-groups/\" target=\"_blank\">Dura-Ace</a>, again splitting the difference of its two big dropbar competitors. Besides being made-in-Europe which a lot of traditionalists love, the new wireless Record 13 platform offers a lot of value in its ability to be adapted specifically to how you ride – whether that’s pure road, various mixed surface all-road and gravel mentalities, or a dedicated off-road gravel style.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Everything you loved from Super Record 13 wireless, but still couldn’t afford…</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-19.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-19-1536x1024.jpg\" alt=\"Campagnolo Record rear derailleur\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-19-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-19-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-19-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-19-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-19-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-19-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-19-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-19-1350x900.jpg 1350w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-20.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-20-1536x1024.jpg\" alt=\"Campagnolo Record front derailleur\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-20-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-20-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-20-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-20-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-20-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-20-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-20-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-20-1350x900.jpg 1350w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>All the key features of Campagnolo’s top-tier wireless 13-speed groupset trickle down to Record 13.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You get the same made in-house in Italy ethos. The same fast-shifting electronics inside, and the same removable, rechargeable 750km-range batteries that are different front &amp; rear to not anger SRAM’s AXS patents. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Plus, this latest generation of battery has direct USB-C ports on them, which make charging much easier to manage!</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-22.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2500\" height=\"1667\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-22.jpg\" alt=\"Campagnolo Record rear derailleur\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-22.jpg 2500w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-22-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-22-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-22-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-22-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-22-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-22-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-22-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-22-1350x900.jpg 1350w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Record 13 derailleurs still get the mix of carbon-reinforced polyamide upper &amp; lower knuckles and outer pulley cage, connected with alloy links. But now with a stamped inner steel cage delivers “exceptional lightness, strength, and reliability.” </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Plus, the 14-tooth narrow-wide pulleys now feature durable sealed stainless steel bearings which help lower costs.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-13-e1777369743185.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-13-e1777369743185.jpg\" alt=\"Campagnolo Record rear derailleur gravel\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-13-e1777369743185.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-13-e1777369743185-297x178.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-13-e1777369743185-1536x922.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-13-e1777369743185-120x72.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-13-e1777369743185-768x461.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-13-e1777369743185-1500x900.jpg 1500w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Both the all-road and gravel derailleurs feature the same Nano Clutch for chain retention. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-14.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2500\" height=\"1667\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-14.jpg\" alt=\"Campagnolo Record Rear Derailleur gravel 1x\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-14.jpg 2500w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-14-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-14-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-14-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-14-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-14-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-14-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-14-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-14-1350x900.jpg 1350w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>And the gravel 1x-specific Record X gravel derailleur adds the longer cage and 12T &amp; 16T pulley configuration to work with cassettes up to 48 teeth, again with a carbon outer and steel inner cage.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-21.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2500\" height=\"1667\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-21.jpg\" alt=\"Campagnolo Record cassette\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-21.jpg 2500w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-21-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-21-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-21-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-21-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-21-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-21-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-21-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-21-1350x900.jpg 1350w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Cassette-wide, Record 13 cassette continues the tightly-spaced 13-speed gearing steps from Super Record. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>For Record 13 you can pick from 10-33T, 11-36T, and 10-48T options depending on the rear derailleur you select. The new cassettes feature the same low-friction Black Chrome finish as <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/campagnolo-super-record-13-wireless-2x13-speed-road-groupset-is-lighter-faster-more-affordable-and-coming-to-gravel-soon/\" target=\"_blank\">SR</a> on the smaller cogs, and then a new darker Satin Black finish to the upper cogs that is said to “<em>enhance resistance to wear</em>“. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Plus, new Campagnolo Record 13 is fully compatible with the original Super Record 13 cassettes, and those extra premium <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/campagnolo-super-record-gets-ultra-upgrade-with-lighter-carbon-titanium-ceramics/\" target=\"_blank\">Ultra 13</a> ones, too.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>New Record Ergopowers, same classic Campy control</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Campagnolo-Record-13-at-Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor_new-wireless-ergopower-levers.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2100\" height=\"1400\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Campagnolo-Record-13-at-Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor_new-wireless-ergopower-levers.jpg\" alt=\"Campagnolo Record 13 wireless ergopower levers\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Campagnolo-Record-13-at-Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor_new-wireless-ergopower-levers.jpg 2100w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Campagnolo-Record-13-at-Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor_new-wireless-ergopower-levers-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Campagnolo-Record-13-at-Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor_new-wireless-ergopower-levers-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Campagnolo-Record-13-at-Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor_new-wireless-ergopower-levers-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Campagnolo-Record-13-at-Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor_new-wireless-ergopower-levers-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Campagnolo-Record-13-at-Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor_new-wireless-ergopower-levers-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Campagnolo-Record-13-at-Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor_new-wireless-ergopower-levers-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Campagnolo-Record-13-at-Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor_new-wireless-ergopower-levers-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Campagnolo-Record-13-at-Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor_new-wireless-ergopower-levers-1350x900.jpg 1350w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The new Record 13 Ergopower shift brake controls are functionally the same as Super Record, keeping the classic Campy thumb button that got a huge functional boost with Super Record.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Campagnolo-Record-13-at-Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor_left-wireless-ergopower-front.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1500\" height=\"2000\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Campagnolo-Record-13-at-Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor_left-wireless-ergopower-front.jpg\" alt=\"Campagnolo Record 13 wireless ergopower shifter, adjustable lever blade\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Campagnolo-Record-13-at-Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor_left-wireless-ergopower-front.jpg 1500w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Campagnolo-Record-13-at-Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor_left-wireless-ergopower-front-225x300.jpg 225w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Campagnolo-Record-13-at-Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor_left-wireless-ergopower-front-90x120.jpg 90w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Campagnolo-Record-13-at-Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor_left-wireless-ergopower-front-768x1024.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Campagnolo-Record-13-at-Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor_left-wireless-ergopower-front-1152x1536.jpg 1152w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Campagnolo-Record-13-at-Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor_left-wireless-ergopower-front-675x900.jpg 675w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Campagnolo-Record-13-at-Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor_left-wireless-ergopower-side.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1500\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Campagnolo-Record-13-at-Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor_left-wireless-ergopower-side.jpg\" alt=\"Campagnolo Record 13 wireless ergopower shifter\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Campagnolo-Record-13-at-Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor_left-wireless-ergopower-side.jpg 1500w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Campagnolo-Record-13-at-Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor_left-wireless-ergopower-side-297x297.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Campagnolo-Record-13-at-Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor_left-wireless-ergopower-side-120x120.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Campagnolo-Record-13-at-Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor_left-wireless-ergopower-side-768x768.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Campagnolo-Record-13-at-Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor_left-wireless-ergopower-side-900x900.jpg 900w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You still get easy reach adjust, and the latest simple, hollowed out shift paddles.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-25-e1777370018146.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1667\" height=\"1667\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-25-e1777370018146.jpg\" alt=\"Campagnolo Record shifter\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-25-e1777370018146.jpg 1667w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-25-e1777370018146-297x297.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-25-e1777370018146-1536x1536.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-25-e1777370018146-120x120.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-25-e1777370018146-768x768.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-25-e1777370018146-900x900.jpg 900w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Inside, in addition to the inner thumb shift lever, there’s also the same customizable Smart Button at the top of the hood, plus the inner Mode button &amp; LED indicator.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-23.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-23-1536x1024.jpg\" alt=\"Campagnolo Record front brake\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-23-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-23-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-23-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-23-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-23-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-23-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-23-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-23-1350x900.jpg 1350w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-27.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-27-1536x1024.jpg\" alt=\"Campagnolo Record rear brake\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-27-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-27-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-27-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-27-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-27-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-27-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-27-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-27-1350x900.jpg 1350w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The hydraulic brake system inside remains unchanged from Super Record, and pairs with the same excellent disc brake power and modulation, as before. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Again, the only difference is in the same matte/gloss finish like you’ll find on the new Record brake levers.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>What’s new &amp; different?</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-16.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2500\" height=\"1667\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-16.jpg\" alt=\"Campagnolo Record wide range cassette gravel\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-16.jpg 2500w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-16-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-16-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-16-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-16-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-16-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-16-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-16-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-16-1350x900.jpg 1350w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The key differences are almost entirely in more careful and more affordable material choices and simpler finishes. Think: less use of titanium and more steel or aluminum. And less extensive machining away of excess material like in the new Record cassette.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The end result being an extra 208-342g of material, depending on which Record 13 configuration you choose over Super Record 13. But always the same performance. <br /></p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Campagnolo Record – Options, pricing &amp; weight comparisons, and availability</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-24.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2500\" height=\"1667\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-24.jpg\" alt=\"Campagnolo Record crank arm\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-24.jpg 2500w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-24-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-24-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-24-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-24-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-24-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-24-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-24-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Sea-Otter-2026-Bikerumor-24-1350x900.jpg 1350w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>As a baseline setup, this new Campagnolo Record groupset sells for 2700€ in a traditional road 2×13 build, without a powermeter. That’s 1600€ less (&lt;37%) than Super Record. The Record 2×13 configuration has a claimed weight of 2783g (vs. 2441g for SR).</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For a gravel comparison, the new Campagnolo Record X groupset sells for 2130€ in a 1×13 build, with a Nano Clutched rear derailleur and also without a powermeter. That’s 1245€ less (again &lt;37%) than Super Record X. The Record X 1×13 configuration has a claimed weight of 2777g (vs. 2569g for SR).</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The road/all-road, clutched 1x with a smaller road cassette is the lightest of the new platform, with a claimed weight of 2656g and a price tag of 2335€. The road/all-road, clutched 2x again with the small cassette weighs a claimed weight of 2806g and a price of 2765€. And lastly, the road/all-road, clutched Record X 1x with the wide range cassette has a claimed weight of 2820g and the same 2129€ price as the gravel-specific version.</p>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Campagnolo-Record-13-wireless_1x-crankset.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1000\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Campagnolo-Record-13-wireless_1x-crankset.jpg\" alt=\"Campagnolo Record 13 wireless, simple 1x crankset\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Campagnolo-Record-13-wireless_1x-crankset.jpg 1600w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Campagnolo-Record-13-wireless_1x-crankset-297x186.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Campagnolo-Record-13-wireless_1x-crankset-1536x960.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Campagnolo-Record-13-wireless_1x-crankset-120x75.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Campagnolo-Record-13-wireless_1x-crankset-768x480.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Campagnolo-Record-13-wireless_1x-crankset-1440x900.jpg 1440w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Even though that Record X crank we got a look at (<em>above</em>) kind of seems like it, that is not the powermeter crankset, but rather the 1x-specific Record X crankset used for 1x gravel, road &amp; even TT builds. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Campagnolo-Record-2x-and-1x-13-speed-PWM-powermeter-cranksets.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2500\" height=\"1407\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Campagnolo-Record-2x-and-1x-13-speed-PWM-powermeter-cranksets.jpg\" alt=\"new carbon Campagnolo Record 13 wireless 1x &amp; 2x power meter cranksets\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Campagnolo-Record-2x-and-1x-13-speed-PWM-powermeter-cranksets.jpg 2500w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Campagnolo-Record-2x-and-1x-13-speed-PWM-powermeter-cranksets-297x167.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Campagnolo-Record-2x-and-1x-13-speed-PWM-powermeter-cranksets-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Campagnolo-Record-2x-and-1x-13-speed-PWM-powermeter-cranksets-120x68.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Campagnolo-Record-2x-and-1x-13-speed-PWM-powermeter-cranksets-768x432.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Campagnolo-Record-2x-and-1x-13-speed-PWM-powermeter-cranksets-2048x1153.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Campagnolo-Record-2x-and-1x-13-speed-PWM-powermeter-cranksets-1200x675.jpg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Campagnolo-Record-2x-and-1x-13-speed-PWM-powermeter-cranksets-1600x900.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Campagnolo uses the same modular right-side direct-mount Record crank arm for both this 1x spider and their spider-based powermeter. Interestingly, the new Record-level PWN power meter now sells for just 600€ extra over a conventional setup. That’s a huge 567€ savings (a 49% reduction) vs. the SR HPPM, made possible with “<em>simplified electronics</em>” that maintain +/-2% accuracy claims.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Record 2×13 Road, Record X 1×13 Gravel, and Record X 1×13 Road builds are all available starting today. As are the power meters. The Road/All-Road 1x &amp; 2x versions with the Nano Clutch derailleur, designed to be used with conventional smaller cassettes, will be available in July 2026. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"http://Campaganolo.com\" target=\"_blank\">Campaganolo.com</a></em></p>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/campagnolo-record-13-wireless-road-and-gravel-groupset/\">Campy Record Expands Italian Wireless 13sp Gruppo Platform at 37% Lower Price than SR!</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Cory Benson","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"58262f642a5e44f40a709efdba5d7d213970547194574140bc95af61d91fac75","category":"Cycling"}